genresAdvancedInfo.name: house argentino
genresAdvancedInfo.description: House Argentino is a subgenre of house music that originated in Argentina in the 1990s. It is characterized by its fusion of electronic beats with traditional Argentine musical styles, such as tango and folk music. House Argentino often features live instrumentation, including bandoneóns and guitars, as well as electronic elements. It has become a popular genre in Argentina and has influenced the development of other Latin American electronic genres.
